The strike was over the perceived failure to implement a pact signed with the government in March which involved a pay rise for Kenya University Staff Union (Kusu) members.
Residents pelted a police vehicle with stones and barricaded the Mombasa-Malindi road in Kilifi town following the shooting of a man by a prison warder.
Residents of Utalii in Mathare rioted and burned tires to protest against the repeating of ODM nominations.
The police shot into the air to disperse a crowd of rioting youths at a political rally in Meru.

Herders in Bambo, Mandera, have discovered five bodies buried in a shallow grave.The locals exhumed the bodies on Monday [3 July] morning and took them to Lafey Hospital.Medical personnel at the hospital told Nation.co.ke that a male body had bullet wounds in the forehead and the other bodies appeared to have been strangled.The five were from Fino Ward but their bodies were found in Warankara Ward about 65 kilometres away.

Youths injured an NTV cameraman and stoned vehicles after a rally addressed by Nasa leader Raila Odinga in Migori town ended. At least 10 vehicles were pelted with stones, including one belonging to the Nation Media Group. The youths barricaded the road at Posta roundabout and attacked motorists on the highway. Police used teargas to disperse them.

Arrests: Police have arrested 27 armed youth said to have been planning to disrupt a political rally in Rabuor, Kisumu County. Several crude weapons, including three machetes and two knives, and two rolls of bhang were found.
Police arrested 27 youths armed with crude weapons, who were planning to disrupt a NASA rally in Nyando.
The Kenyan security forces rescued 2 of the 4 pupils kidnapped during the Al Shabaab attack on Kiunga two days previously. No reports of clashes.
Youths suspected to be part of the outlawed Mungiki militia kill a butcher and torch houses in Embakasi. The attack was believed to be over a land dispute.
Residents of Handege shopping centre in Gatundu South, protested and blocked the Gatundu-Karinga -Flyover road demanding that speed bumps be erected.

Eight people including four school children and four police officers were killed in a roadside bomb attack planted by suspected Al Shabaab fighters that occurred in Kiunga, Lamu on Tuesday. The police officers were escorting the school children to Kiunga from Mararani, when the lorry was hit by an IED. Following the blast, al Shabaab opened fire on the victims.

assoc_actor_1: NASA: National Super Alliance; ODM: Orange Democratic Movement
notes: ODM and NASA youths rioted at Raila Odinga's rally in Rarieda. The police dispersed the crowd with teargas.

The county commander said several people have been arrested in connection with an attack on a lorry carrying camels along Laisamis Road. One person was killed. The attackers transferred the animals to another truck and drove off.

A 12 year old boy was beheaded by raiders on Sunday morning in Saku constituency. Another person was seriously injured during the attack. The attack is suspected to be linked to recent violence between the Rendille and Borana communities.

Residents in Tharaka-Nithi County set up road blocks on the Meru-Nairobi highway demanding that speed bumps be built after a boy was knocked down by a lorry on Monday. Police were deployed in the area to disperse the crowd
A secondary school student was shot dead by suspected Pokot cattle rustlers in Kaben, Marakwet East at 8am.
Youth in Meru lit born fires and barricaded the Meru-Embu highway in protest over the construction of a road. Anti-riot police dispersed the crowd by using teargas.
Jubilee and KANU supporters clashed during a rally led by Uasin Gishu Governor Jackson Mandago in Kabarnet, Baringo on Saturday.
Five people were killed when Al Shabaab atacked the Equity bank In Elwak Town.
Police officers exchanged fire with Al Shabaab after they attacked the Equity Back in Elwak Town. Five police reported dead.
A group of elderly women from Ngangarithi held a protest against grabbing of a wetland by private developers.
An Improvised Device (IED) exploded when a vehicle ran over it. The vehicle was heading to Mandera from Elwak. No one was injured in the attack.
Police were forced to fire gunshots in the air after youth took advantage of the crowds to steal from those gathered to hear Kenneth speak.
200 survivors of the 2008 election violence in Kiambaa gathered to call on politicians to avoid hate speech in the election campaign.
One criminal was shot dead by police officers at Hongera in Kisauni, Mombasa County.
Two suspected criminals were killed in Mishomoroni by a mob.
An Administration Police officer shot dead two of his colleagues in Baringo County, in unclear circumstances.
Arrests: Police have arrested more than 80 people suspected to be "terrorists" in Eastleigh.

Residents protest over preparations for Uhuru visit to Murang'a. They blocked roads leading to the town on Tuesday morning and demanded to have the road reconstructed. Police intervened to stop the protest

Students from Kirimon Primary School in Samburu West Sub County attacked and injured three female teachers in protest against being punished by female teachers. The school was closed after the attack.

Students from Kirimon Primary School in Samburu West Sub County attacked and injured three female teachers in protest against being punished by female teachers. The school was closed after the attack. Police are injured when they try to rescue the beseiged teachers.
Nine Kenyan soldiers were killed, and ten others were injured when a road side bomb explosed. Al Shabaab confirmed claimed responsibility of the attack.
One person has been killed and about 500 cattle stolen by suspected bandits along the West Pokot-Turkana border. Thsi is believed to be part of a dispute between Pokot and Turkana communities.
Residents of Muhoroni took to the streets to protest against the candidature of former MP Ayiecho Olweny.
NASA and Jubilee supporters clashed and threw stones at each other during Odinga's rally in Mutuati, in Meru.
Youth in Kitui were injured in a riot for cash thrown by politicians at a rally.
Four cilivilians killed and 11 injured when a passenger bus struck a roadside bomb suspected to have been planted by Al Shabaab between Lafey and Elwak in Madera county.
A Boda Boda rider was killed by unidentified assailants over the management of campaign money for a local politician.
Students barricaded Jogoo road, protesting the bus driver who injured a volunteer who helped them crossed the road. They demanded the government to erect bumps on the road to improve road safety.
In Marakwet East, a man was shot dead on Tuesday afternoon by suspected Pokot bandits.
Supporters of an independent candidate rioted in Iten prior to the arrival of Kenyatta for a political rally.

A police officer is admitted Nyahururu hospital after he was shot by herders during a security operation to remove illegal herders from the Laikipia Nature Conservancy. The herders and police engaged in a gun battle.

Kanu and Jubilee supporters have clashed in Makutano town in Kapenguria, West Pokot ahead of President Uhuru Kenyatta's visit later today. One person has been injured and rushed to hospital. Police intervened to disperse the crowd.
Political parties clashed in Thika. 1 person was injured.
Nurses, striking for two weeks, hold a protest in Kisumu.
Nurses, striking for two weeks, hold a protest in Nairobi.
A NASA senatorial aspirant is attacked by a crowd and deeply cut by a machete.
A KDF convoy was transporting military supplies to Somalia when it was targeted in a massive roadside explosion, just outside of Liboi town. Several soldiers wounded.
Detonation: The IED planted by Al Shabaab, and targeting Kenya Defence Forces (KDF) along the Milimani-Baure's supply route detonated without any casualties or injuries on the side of KDF.
Six people were killed and several others injured after armed Pokot bandits attacked Lokori in Turkana South on Saturday.

actor1: Police Forces of Kenya (2013-) General Service Unit
notes: A member of the GSU is non-fatally shot by 'bandits'.
Youths tried to attack Nyando MP Fred Outa at a funeral on Saturday.Some of the locals started heckling speakers, demanding that Governor Jack Ranguma addresses the ceremony in Ahero.

Two people were killed and three others injured after about 200 armed bandits attacked Kamuge village in Turkana East. The bandits are said to be from Baringo East. Police reservists responded and exchange of fire with the bandits.
Matatu operators blocked sections of Moi Avenue in protest of officers demanding money from them everyday.The protests caused traffic until the police dispersed the protests

Raiders from Isiolo attacked an Administration Police (AP) camp at Mlango, about 30 kilometres from Isiolo Town. At the same time, five people were shot dead during a battle between police and armed communal militia at Mlango in Burat Ward, Isiolo County, who had stolen cattle. The militiamen were believed to be from Isolio and Samburu counties.
"Rogue" bus conductors block Tom Mboya street in protest of an unknown issue.
A journalist was attacked by a politician's bodyguards.

Unknown gunmen shot dead one person and injured another in Mandera country near the Somalia border. The attackers targeted the vehicle belonging to a local political aspirant Mohamed Abdi who was not in the convoy of the two cars headed to El Wak town.
Nurses protested at the County Referral Hospital in Voi. Wards remained deserted as patients were collected by relatives.

At least three people were killed after a car they were travelling in hit a landmine along Dadaab-Kulan road in Garissa County [eastern Kenya]. Al Shabaab believed responsible. One person escaped with injuries. The Star reports four dead.
The inhabitants of Eldama Ravine attacked 2 teenage boys and a man who they accused of stealing cattle. One of the boys was lynched and the others were severely injured.
On Monday, a team of security officers escaped an IED explosion unhurt as they hunted down a group of al-Shabab militants who had planted landmines in Gerille area, Wajir County.
Nurses in Kisii hold demonstrations to protest failure by the national and county governments to honour CBA

NASA [National Super Alliance] supporters burnt Jubilee campaign materials in Kisii town on Monday [5 June]. They temporarily blocked the road outside the Capital Hotel roundabout as they burnt the posters on the road.
President Kenyatta's convoy faced protests by youth supporting independent candidates in Karatina, Othaya and Nyeri towns.
Dissenting supporters of the Jubilee coalition protested against President Uhuru Kenyatta and his deputy William Ruto over their interference in local intra-Jubilee electoral contests
Jubilee and NASA supporters clashed at a rally in Kapsabet.

One person was killed and several others injured on Friday in clashes between rival political groups in Bungoma county in Western Kenya. The two groups engaged in violent confrontations after their candidates were cleared by the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) to contest in the Aug. 8 general elections. Police fired teargas to disperse them.
Silent protests against Kenyatta and Ruto over the results of the primaries. In Laikipia, hundreds of residents carried the banners of independent Nderitu Mureithi.
President Kenyatta's convoy faced protests by youth supporting independent candidates in Karatina, Othaya and Nyeri towns
Silent protests against Kenyatta and Ruto over the results of the Jubilee primaries. In Ol Kalou in Nyandarua County, hundreds of residents carried Wanjiku Muhia's banners.
President Kenyatta's convoy faced protests by youth supporting independent candidates in Karatina, Othaya and Nyeri towns
Al-Shabaab militants burned down a school and abducted two teachers in an overnight attack in Fafi, Garissa. One teacher is killed.
Two motorists were shot and severely injured during a demonstration against police officers in Moyale town.
Seven police officers and a civilian were killed when an armoured vehicle drove over a roadside bomb in southeastern Kenya. Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility
An explosive device aimed at a military lorry went off between Kiunga and Ishakani. It exploded early and there were no casualties.

Two soldiers from Kenya Defence forces were killed, and another wounded in an IED explosion. Al-Shabaab claimed responibility of the attack. Another IED exploded in the same area on the same day before a Kenyan vehicle passed, leaving the passengers unharmed.
ANC party representative's supporters protested against the Independent Electoral Commission (IEBC) after the candidate's name was missing from the IEBC register list.

Lamu residents demonstrated in Malindi on 30/05/2017 against a court case regarding a wind energy project in Baharini in Mpeketoni, Lamu. They called for a withdrawal of a case on land set aside for the project and protesting against the delays that the court case will cause to the project. No fatalities nor injuries are reported.

Students of the Laikipia University (the main campus is located 11km from Nyahururu) protested against the rise in student fees on 29/05/2017. As Vice Chancelor (VC) refused to meet the protesting students, the students started to throw stones and took the streets. VC called the police to disperse them. No fatalities reported.
Three suspected Al-Shaabab militants were killed in a gun battle with police in Tana River County on Monday.
Supporters of NASA and Jubilee threw stones at each other outside Kenyatta International Conference Centre (KICC) as President Uhuru Kenyatta presented his papers to the electoral body for clearance.

1 student was killed and scores of students were injured when a fire broke out at a school in Bondo. The fire is believed to be linked to election-based protests that had broken out in the school some weeks previously.
Three rangers were shot dead and five others seriously injured by Moran local fighters on Sunday
A man was shot dead by a gang in Mai Mahiu on 26/05/2017. The police has yet to establish the motive of the killing.
Three Al-Shabaab militants shot dead a Tana River County Assembly driver on Friday

Herders from Isiolo and Marsabit are feared dead as they engaged each other in a deadly gun battle throughout Friday. Residents from the two sides said the herders exchanged fire that led to deaths estimated to be over 10 people. Both sides had casualties, but the Isiolo side reportedly lost more men.
Violence broke out as hundreds of K'Oyoo's supporters, lit twigs and blocked roads to protest the absence of his name as a candidate on the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC)s.
Youth in Oyugis rioted at the campaign rally of the Homa Bay governor. The police dispersed the crowd with teargas.

At last five police officers were killed and one other injured after an Improvised Explosive Devise tore their vehicle along the Malelei-Kulan Road in Liboi, Garissa County. Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility of the attacks

Two people were injured after supporters of Tharaka-Nithi Governor Samuel Ragwa and Chuka/Igambang'ombe MP Muthomi Njuki clashed at Marimanti town. The group supporting MP Muthomi marched on the highway waving placards against Governor Ragwa. The group supporting Mr Ragwa ran after the other group hurling stones.
Women protest demanding a man accused of sodomising local children be convicted and jailed.
Property destruction: Over 100 camels have been killed and at least 47 houses torched by bandits who locals believe are security officers on the border of Kitui and Tana River counties.
3 rangers were killed in a battle with Moran cattle raiders in Archers Post.
On 24 May, two police officers were killed in an explosion between Malelei and Kulan in Garissa, near Hagadera refugee camp
At least three policemen were killed in an IED explosions in Liboi, Garissa County, near the Kenya - Somalia border. Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility of the attacks.

At least five policemen were killed in an IED explosions in Mandera, near the Kenya - Somalia border. Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility of the attacks. Police later arrested several Al-Shabaab suspects behind the attacks in Mandera county. One of the susptect is a high ranking Al-Shabaab explosives expert

Land invaders suspected to be from Baringo County attacked residents on 23 May at Rubere in Laikipia West. The "bandits" paralysed a security meeting by shooting in the air, dispersing the residents and security officers. Several residents were injured as they scampered for safety.
Presiding Officers (POs) and clerks who oversaw Jubilee party's primaries took to the streets of Kericho town to protest the party's bureaucracy and delays in paying them their salaries.

Supporters of Gilgil MP Mathenge Ndiritu blocked access on the Nairobi-Nakuru highway as they were protesting over the outcome of the recent Jubilee primaries.They accused Jubilee of imposing a leader on them after Ndiritu's rival, Martha Wangari, was declared the winner. Riot police intervened and cleared the protest.

Traders protested demolition of their stalls in Mombasa on 23/05/2017. They barricaded a road with logs and bonfires. The anti-riot team of the Kenyan police forces used tear gas to disperse the demonstrators. No fatalities.
Angry villagers in Korando, Kisumu West, rioted when police tried to exhume the body of a man involved in a land dispute.
Hundreds of coffee farmers in Embu County held demonstrations at Manyatta market, protesting delays in paying their salaries.
Striking nurses protest in Nyeri town on May 22, 2017

assoc_actor_1: Jubilee Coalition; PDR: Party of Development and Reforms
notes: Supporters of Isiolo Governor Godana Doyo (Party for Development and Reforms - PDR), Senator Mohammed Kuti (Independent) and Abdul Bahari (Jubilee) hurled stones at each other ahead of President Uhuru Kenyatta's political rally. A Jubilee supporter was shot dead by the police when a Jubilee rally in Isiolo turned violent.

Residents blocked Churo-Loruk road to register their disappointment with the police after Churo Amaiya MCA Thomas Minito was found dead on 19 May 2017. Residents armed with crude weapons kicked out journalists who had visited MCA Minito's home, accusing the media of not vibrantly publishing issues that affect the Pokot community such as insecurity and killings of leaders and civilians. They also torched a neighbour's house while protesting the death of MCA Thomas Munito.

assoc_actor_2: FORD-Kenya: Forum for the Restoration of Democracy-Kenya
notes: In Bungoma, a campaigner of governor challenger Wycliffe Wangamati was seriously injured in an attack in Webuye. Mr Joseph Kubende was driving to his home on Friday night when his car was blocked by a Probox whose occupants pulled him out and hit him with a blunt object on the head.
Dr Thuo Mathenge and his supporters protest outside Jubilee Party headquarters in Pangani on April 19, 2017 over the outcome of Nyeri governorship nomination.
Supporters of Murang'a governorship aspirant Mwangi wa Iria protest outside Milimani Law Courts in Nairobi on May 19, 2017

Scores of residents took to the streets in support of area Jubilee gubernatorial candidate, Anne Waiguru, from claims that she was involved in the NYS scandal. The residents, who held a peaceful demonstration in Kutus town, accused MPs who want Waiguru barred from vying for the seat in August of having a sinister agenda. Led by the county Jubilee interim committee treasurer, Rose Njeru, the protestors warned that they would disrupt polls in the county if Waiguru was barred.

The Churo/Amaya ward MCA, Thomas Minito, was reportedly approached by three people at a hotel in Kabarnet town on Tuesday afternoon when he was having lunch with a government official from Tiaty. His body was on Thursday evening found floating in River Athi just under the Donyo Sabuk bridge in Machakos County Reports indicate that the body was retrieved and a small poster found in his coat pocket bearing his name.

One person has been shot dead in Kerio Valley by cattle rustlers. The rustlers also stole over 40 goats and cattle during the Thursday afternoon attack.They also killed two goats. Elgeyo Marakwet Police Commander Tom Odera said efforts to apprehend the culprits are ongoing.
Riots in Tharaka-Nithi lead to Tigania West deputy county commissioner Alfred Makau getting hit by a stone
Ward representatives in Turkana, who were angry about the dispersal of funds, rioted and locked the civil servants out of the Turkana government offices.

Chaos has rocked Kaboto market after Tharaka-Nithi and Meru leaders clashed over the border between the two counties. Police officers opened fire to disperse Tharaka residents who accompanied.The angry residents pelted the officers with rocks, smashing the windscreens of several vehicles.

Kakamega journalists held a peaceful demonstration over increasing attacks and threats against them from police and politicians. They demonstrated along the busy Kakamega-Mumias Road from Shianda market to Mumias East Sub-County offices and presented a petition to Deputy County Commissioner Willy Cheboi.

Nation correspondent Shaban Makokha was assaulted by administration police officers at Shianda Trading Centre while photographing youths fighting over money given to them by a politician. The journalist was treated at St Mary's Mission Hospital in Mumias and discharged.

A Kenyan official was killed on Wednesday after a vehicle he was traveling in ran over an improvised explosive device in Elwak area near Kenya-Somalia border. Mandera East divisional police commander Timothy Muasya said the explosive device was buried on the ground by unknown people. The driver survived with serious injuries after the 1 p.m. incident. Police have blamed the attacks on Al-Shabaab militants who are operating in the area.

The Kenya County Government Workers Union recalled all their Nairobi members from their work station on Wednesday morning to hold a protest march at City Hall. The workers are protesting over unpaid April salaries, although the county government received Sh1.021 billion from National Treasury on Tuesday to pay off the salaries.
In Homa Bay County, two youths were seriously injured in Kendu Bay town after supporters of governor Cyprian Awiti and those of Kasipul MP Oyugi Magwanga clashed. Four youths were arrested.

A security operation is underway in Mandera town [northeastern Kenya] after a chief said to be instrumental in the war against terror was gunned down by people believed to be al-Shabab militia. The heavily armed al-Shabab militants are said to have raided the home of the chief in Omar Jillo location, Lafey sub-county in Mandera East before killing him on the spot. The military and the police have teamed up in an operation to comb Mandera in search of the assailants
At least four people died on Tuesday when their vehicle set off an improvised explosive device in a small Kenyan town near the border with Somalia, police said.Al-Shabaab militants were suspected
Suspected Al Shabaab militants attacked a village in Mandera and killed a chief before abducting two police reservists on Monday night.

Angry youth on Monday blocked the busy Nairobi-Mombasa highway at Caltex area in Voi, Taita Taveta County protesting against unemployment at the Standard Gauge Railway Site at Kasarani area. They burnt tires along the highway. Police intervened to disperse them and arrested seven. The demonstration halted traffic flow along the busy highway forcing motorists delay their journey for hours.

An Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) party director of communications Philip Etale was attacked with pepper spray by an unknown group in Nairobi's city centre. He was rushed to Nairobi hospital, where he was treated and discharged later
Property destruction: Al Shabaab militants destroyed a communications mast in Wajir
The local MCA was abducted by unidentified attackers. The police did not file a report. His body was found five days later.

There was drama on Mbagathi Road Monday when pupils from Kenyatta Golf Course Academy blocked the highway to protest demolition of their school.The pupils placed their desks across the road and sat on them, blocking traffic in the morning rush hour before they voluntarily moved away to give way to motorists.They demonstrated outside the school with their parents who expressed frustration as they had already paid fees.

Two more people have been killed in fresh attacks by bandits at Kasiluni in Kitui County [eastern Kenya], a week after a similar attack in the same area. The two were ambushed separately and shot in their farms on Sunday [14 May] in the volatile area, which borders Mwingi Game Reserve, bringing the number of people killed in the last week to four.
Youths at an ODM meeting in Kakamega assaulted Nation journalist Linet Wafula and destroyed her phone. No serious injuries reported.

Member of County Assembly aspirant's three sons were found dead. The second was discovered on Wednesday, retrieved the same day and taken to the same hospital mortuary in the evening. The third was found on 18/05. The trio were missing since at least 14/05, when they failed to arrive at a church service. The children's disappearance may be related to politics.
residents of Engineer protest against the issuance of Jubilee Certificate to incumbent Wanjiku Muhia who had allegedly lost to Faith Gitau during Women Rep nominations.

One person was shot dead and another injured during protests in Nyandarua town on Saturday evening. Anti-riot police were forced to fire in the air to disperse the residents who accused the Judiciary of overturning the will of the people.The residents were protesting the issuance of Jubilee Certificate to incumbent Wanjiku Muhia who had allegedly lost to Faith Gitau during Women Rep nominations.

Heavily-armed al-Shabab mujahideen movement forces have launched a major attack on a village on the outskirts of the city of Garissa [northeast Kenya].Reports from the Somali-dominated NFD [Northern Frontier Districts] of Kenya say the attack caused heavy casualties.Kenyan government officials have not officially commented on the death toll from the attack. Sources say al-Shabab forces seized control of the village, known as Amuma, with Kenyan police officials also confirming the attack to the media.

Youth in Mumias on Saturday afternoon took to the streets burning Jubilee T-shirts and other campaign material while chanting pro-Nasa slogans moments after Deputy President William Ruto toured the region.The protests came a few minutes after Mr Ruto had finished addressing hundreds of residents in Bomani in Mumias. The rowdy youth, who went about harassing anyone wearing Jubilee regalia, termed the region a Nasa zone.The demonstrators blamed the Jubilee government for the high cost of living and the woes facing Mumias Sugar Company.
Police use live bullets against rioters barricading the road in the Fly Over area (Ruai) in the outskirts of Nairobi. A person is killed in the cross fire.

residents of Kinangop protest against the issuance of Jubilee Certificate to incumbent Wanjiku Muhia who had allegedly lost to Faith Gitau during Women Rep nominations. The protesters engage in running battles with police.
residents of Ndarangwa protest against the issuance of Jubilee Certificate to incumbent Wanjiku Muhia who had allegedly lost to Faith Gitau during Women Rep nominations.
residents of Ol Kalou protest against the issuance of Jubilee Certificate to incumbent Wanjiku Muhia who had allegedly lost to Faith Gitau during Women Rep nominations.
residents of Miharati protest against the issuance of Jubilee Certificate to incumbent Wanjiku Muhia who had allegedly lost to Faith Gitau during Women Rep nominations.

Supporters of Governor Isaac Rutto (CCM) and National Assembly Deputy Speaker Joyce Laboso (Jubilee) clashed at the funeral in Olbutyo on 13/05/2017. The source does not report any fatalities but one man was seriously injured.
Two quarry workers were shot dead Friday and one was missing in a suspected extremist attack in Kenya's northern county of Mandera, a government official said.
Riots in Nakuru over an unspecified issue
Unidentified people wielding machetes destroyed a candidate's billboard.

Aspiring Woman Representative Esther Passaris (ODM) was held hostage for several hours by "goons" at University of Nairobi. The attackers were known to be led by a student who was a member of the local County Assembly (political affiliation not known) and demanded a large amount of money for release. The attackers were said to have attacked the candidate, her bodyguards and threatened to burn cars. The leader of the attackers was later arrested and the candidate was freed.

University students from around the country protested against the employment policy of the Standard Gauge Railway construction in Voi on 12/05/2017. They blocked the Nairobi-Mombasa highway, accusing the China Roads and Bridges Company of employing foreigners, even though the President had ordered the company employ locals. Seven youth were arrested by the police, because of blocking the highway. No fatalities.

Residents of Aguthi Gaki ward in Tetu constituency, Nyeri County, destroyed water pipes as they demonstrated against an irrigation project in the neighbouring Mathira constituency.The residents say they will not benefit from the project though the pipes pass through their ward.Led by Tetu Jubilee parliamentary aspirant Mwangi Gichuhi, the residents uprooted the pipes and said no work will proceed until an agreement between the two constituencies is honoured.
Two people are shot and killed by raids on their farms by unidentified communal gunmen

Al Shabaab militants raided Omar Jilo, in northern Kenya, where they clashed with police forces. 2 local administrators were killed and 2 police reservists were abducted. Security personnel are pursuing the attackers.

Medical interns posted in government hospitals across the country have protested against the reversal without explanation of salaries that were paid into their bank accounts "last week." (Source dated 16/05) At least 335 out of a total 725 interns posted in different State hospitals are pointing fingers at their employer, the Ministry of Health, for the confusion.

Further reports have emerged of the damage caused by an explosion that targeted a Kenyan army convoy in Garissa County, northeastern Kenya. The explosion which was a land mine attack was targeted on a Kenya army convoy in between Liboi town and Kulan village in Garissa county. Kenyan police said the explosion injured several soldiers with three sustaining serious injuries. The injured were airlifted to a hospital in the capital, Nairobi, for treatment. No one who has claimed responsibility for the attack given that al-Shabab has severally taken credit for attacks that have happened in northeastern Kenya.

assoc_actor_1: KNUT: Kenya National Union of Teachers
notes: Teachers took to the streets of Iten town to protest an alleged grabbing of 100 acres of land belonging to Prime Time Sacco (PTS), formerly Keiyo Teachers Sacco (KTS). The protest brought teachers from Keiyo and Marakwet with unions from two Sub-Counties meeting in Iten town to fight for their rights in the Eldoret land valued at Sh3 billion. Led by Keiyo Kenya National Union of Teachers (KNUT) Executive Secretary, Musa Busienei, the teachers said they legally purchased the land from National Social Security Fund in 2004 but Kenya Prisons and MTRH later laid claim to the same land.

Cattle rustlers attacked the village of Seretion on 09/05/2017, recovering goats that had been stolen three days earlier. A police reservist and a suspected robber were killed in the shootout. Hundreds of locals are fleeing now to safer places, as similar attacks have taken place in the region recently.

A boda boda rider has died Tuesday morning after a collision with a KDF truck in Isiolo Town.There was tension as angry locals threatened to set a blaze the truck.They were also threatening to lynch the driver of the lorry.Police officers had to shoot in the air to disperse the crowd and allow them to collect the body of the boda boda rider.Two other people were seriously injured in the crash and were rushed to the Isiolo County Referral Hospital.

Njiru residents held demonstration early today in protest of a hit and run accident.The residents claim a young man was last night hit by a driver who did not bother to stop the car or take the man to the hospital.The angry demonstrates blocked the road bringing all activities in the area to a standstill.
Dan Ocholla, a journalist at The Standard, was attacked and seriously injured by Kakamega County soldiers while taking photos of injured workers at a construction site in the town.

source: Xinhua General News Service; Ghana News Agency (GNA)
notes: At least six Kenyan security officers were injured in a bomb blast on Monday in the northeast region of Garissa near the Somali border. Somali militant group Al-Shabaab has claimed responsibility for the attack, saying its fighters killed four government soldiers, including two commanders.
Ngecha residents demonstrated on 07/05/2017 urging the government to prevent crime in the area. The demonstration was sparked by recent murders.
On May 7, Mr Bernard Otieno, 43, was seriously injured after he was attacked at Chemelil market where supporters of Masogo/Nyangoma MCA Samuel Ong'ow and his rival Habil Nyasuna clashed.
Presiding officers and clerks hired by Jubilee Party during the Nakuru County nominations on Friday staged a demonstration to demand for their pay at the party regional headquarters in Milimani.

Cattle rustlers raided the village of Ngaratuko on 06/05/2017. They shot dead two people and stole goats. Due to the recent attacks, many schools are closed and hundreds of locals are fleeing now to safer places.

Demonstrations erupted in Eldoret after it emerged that Jubilee was planning to repeat the primaries at the station. Unknown people attacked three Governor Jackson Mandago's campaigners (Jubilee Party). No fatalities.

Doctors protest over unpaid salaries. Medical interns posted in government hospitals across the country have protested against the reversal without explanation of salaries that were paid into their bank accounts "last week." (Source dated 16/05) At least 335 out of a total 725 interns posted in different State hospitals are pointing fingers at their employer, the Ministry of Health, for the confusion.

In Kondele, Kisumu town, residents of Migosi ward protested against the issuance of a certificate to Pamela Oyoo instead of Victor Rodgers. They lit bonfires and demanded that Rodgers be given the certificate or they would boycott the August polls. They accused ODM board secretary Bob Arunga of rigging out Rodgers.

In Nyando subcounty, residents of Ahero ward took to the streets from 6am, protesting against the issuing of a certificate to Amos Odote. Residents questioned the criteria that the National Elections Board used to award the certificate. They blocked the Ahero-Awasi road and lit bonfires before they stormed the ODM party office and set furniture on fire. They painted the office with Jubilee Party colours and wrote 'Jubilee Party, Uhuru Tena'.

Residents of Molo protest for two days after a rumour that the losing Jubilee candidate was handed the ticket after lodging a complaint to the central party tribunal. The protests were conducted "last week", source dated 13/05. They blocked the busy Nakuru Eldoret highway causing a traffic snarl for over four hours forcing police to lobe teargas canisters in order to disperse them.
Demonstrations were in most of the major towns in Nyandarua on Thursday afternoon following claims a woman representative hopeful rigged nominations.

Looting: Cattle rustlers attacked the village of Chemorongion in April or early May 2017 (the source does not incidate an exact date). The source does not indicate any fatalities or injuries. 300 livestock were stolen.
The announcement that Prof Nyong'o had trounced Governor Jack resulted in protests in an unspecified location.

Residents of Molo protest for two days after a rumour that the losing Jubilee candidate was handed the ticket after lodging a complaint to the central party tribunal. The protests were conducted "last week", source dated 13/05. They blocked the busy Nakuru Eldoret highway causing a traffic snarl for over four hours forcing police to lobe teargas canisters in order to disperse them.
Al Shabaab militants attacked El Wak town. 2 people were killed.
A suspected car thief is attacked and injured by a vigilante mob.
Supporters of candidates who had lost the Jubilee primaries thronged outside the Jubilee headquarters to protest for their candidates.

Transport in Busia Town was disrupted for more than one hour Monday as matatu operators held a demonstration to protest the deplorable condition of the main bus park and roads.The protesters planted banana tubers in numerous potholes around the park and nearby roads.Traders also joined the protest, saying they have been losing customers because the roads are rendered impassable when it rains.
ODM youths protested in Langata when the primary results were announced.
The crowd at a Kilimani polling centre attacked a woman who was believed to have been bribing voters during the ODM primaries, though no reports of injuries sustained.
Residents of Mairo Inya township in Ndaragwa protest along the streets against alleged rigging out of Ndaragwa MP Waweru Ndiritu
ODM youths forced their way into the Ziwani Hall during the primaries in Nairobi. The police forced them out and locked the gates.
Gunmen killed five civilians from Pokot and injured another 3 at Kapedo trading centre. This is believed to be a revenge attack.
Several people were injured Saturday when they were pelted with stones as two political rival groups clashed in Eldoret town.
Youth in Naivasha protested the incumbent governor's defeat in the primaries.

Residents of South Horr protested against the cancellation of the nominations in the Jubilee Coalition primary elections on 28/04/2017. They sat on the border of Samburu and Marsabit counties questioning why the nominations are held in the neighbouring Samburu and all other wards in Marsabit county but not in South Horr. No fatalities. The source does not indicate the exact time of the event.
On April 28, dozens of people were injured as police dispersed residents protesting the declaration of Laikipia governor Joshua Irungu as the Jubilee Party flagbearer.
An Mbita candidate was assaulted in Langata at T-Mall. Police have accused political activist Brian Weke, along with a group of 10 men, of assaulting and attempting to kidnap him.
Morans allegedly raided Kamunge village in the neighbouring Turkana County, killed one person and made away with an unknown number of livestock on Thursday last week.
Jubilee supporters in Itiero, Bomorenda, rioted when the Jubilee primaries winner, George Karina, was announced. Police took charge and ordered all civilians out of the county tallying hall.
There were riots in polling stations around Kitutu Chache, as Jubilee supporters rejected the primaries.
Youth in Imenti South rioted and destroyed ballot boxes because they arrived after the votes had been tallied.
Jubilee supporters protested at polling stations in Kiamaina (south of Gingalili village) over names missing from the register.
Jubilee supporters in Kabazi blocked voting temporarily to protest the low numbers of ballot papers available.
ODM supporters rioted in Kisumu Central when Ken Obura was declared winner of the primaries.
Jubilee supporters in Nairobi protested when Maina Kamanda won the primaries.
One person was stabbed during a confrontation between two rival aspirants along Juja Road on Thursday. The case is under investigations

assoc_actor_1: NASA: National Super Alliance; Vigilante Group (Kenya)
notes: One person is killed during an opposition NASA rally when he was accused of being a pickpocket by the demonstrators.

In Kisumu town, police used teargas canisters to disperse youths who were protesting the award of the ODM ticket to Kisumu central MP Ken Obura.The youths argued that Mr Obura had been rigged in at the expense of Gem Central MCA Fred Ouda. An entourage of boda boda riders led by Kisumu governor Jack Ranguma, who were protesting the win of senator Anyang' Nyong'o for the ODM governorship ticket, were caught in the melee.Hundreds of Mr Ouda's supporters thronged the streets chanting his slogans.

Bishop Margaret Wanjiru, an aspirant for the Nairobi governorship and a group of supporters entered a polling centre and destroyed ballot papers when they complained of a distribution problem. The police arrested Wanjiru.
Voters in Bonchari protested the fact that the incumbent MP was given a direct nomination in the primaries. Voting was suspended.
ODM supporters angry that Millie Odhiambo won the party primaries rioted and burned her home.

A house belonging to Mbita MP Millie Odhiambo was set ablaze on Wednesday as protests erupted in Homa Bay over the ODM party nominations.Ms Odhiambo's home in Koyani village in Lambwe was burnt as residents protested after she was announced winner in the Mbita Constituency ODM nominations. No casualties were reported
There were protests in Kiamaina ward in Bahati following cases of missing names in the register.

Workers and farmers attached to Chemelil Sugar Company have called for resignation of top managers, accusing them of poor performance.The workers, who staged protests said the management and the board have failed to pay farmers and transporters since 2014.
Nyali residents protested the decision of the ODM election tribunal in Mombasa on 26/04/2017. The tribunal recommended repeating Nyali MP nominations.
Jubilee voters in Mvita, Mombasa, protested when they realised that names were missing from the ballot papers.

Police fired shots in the air to quell chaos that erupted in Homa Bay following the declaration of incumbent Governor Cyprian Awiti winner in the Orange Democratic Movement nominations.Police were called in to contain the situation after supporters of his opponents vowed not to accept the result of the hotly contested nomination, in which he was facing off with Kasipul MP Oyugi Magwanga and businessman Sammy Wakiaga

There was chaos at Kanja Primary School in Embu during the Jubilee Party nominations after a group of youths prevented Runyenjes MP Cecily Mbarire from forming a second stream at the centre. The youths protested outside the poll centre and threated to eject Ms Mbarire
ODM supporters at Kariokor polling station protested when the authorities announced that the ODM Nairobi primaries had been cancelled.
Supporters of an Amani Coalition contestant rioted and blocked voting in the ANC primaries in Bwake/Luuya ward.
Voting materials reached polling stations late in the Webuye West ANC primaries, so voters broke the ballot boxes and destroyed the ballot papers in protest.
The Jubilee candidate for Nairobi and a group of her supporters stormed a Nairobi polling station and destroyed ballot papers. The police broke up the protest and arrested her.
Voters tried to raid the DCC's office in Gatundu South when they realised that ballot boxes had gone missing.
Police fired into the air to disperse a rowdy crowd of voters in Kiambu.
In Khalaba township, in Bungoma, supporters of different ANC factions broke into fistfights during the primaries. Several youths were injured.

security guard attached to Mbita MP Millie Odhiambo was injured following violence during ODM nominations in the county on Monday.Chaos erupted after the MP's supporters clashed with those of her opponent James Akali.
Protests in Mwea, Kirinyaga County as voters apprehend returning officer and hand him to over police over allegations of rigging in Jubilee primaries.

Disgruntled voters on Monday burnt ballot papers, protesting against the missing names of eight Member of the County Assembly aspirants.. Moments later, armed security officers arrived to find all the ballot papers completely destroyed
In Homa Bay Town Constituency, chaos erupted at Rodi Primary School polling station when officials decided to use exercise books as ballot papers. Police arrest youth and seize weapons.

Mbita MP Millie Odhiambo reported the death of her "supporter" at Homa Bay Police Station. She reported that he was knocked down by a vehicle belonging to one of her rivals which had been trailing her and attacked hermotorcade.An investigation has been launched.

Political activist Brian Weke was arrested over an alleged attack on an ODM Suba North constituency aspirant.Mr James Akali, who is seeking to dislodge incumbent Millie Odhiambo, was attacked in Nairobi at Lang'ata's T-Mall. He suffered injuries.

assoc_actor_1: ODM: Orange Democratic Movement; Government of Kenya (2013-)
notes: The incumbent MP in Changamwe led a group of rowdy youth in storming polling stations and scaring away voters.

assoc_actor_1: FORD-Kenya: Forum for the Restoration of Democracy-Kenya
notes: FORD-Kenya supporters burned their ballot papers at Masaba primary school, Kiminini after it was learned that other papers were not sent elsewhere in the constituency.

actor2: Police Forces of Kenya (2013-) General Service Unit
notes: GSU officers disperse angry supporters of Nicholas Wanyepe who were on April 23, 2017 protesting at the ODM Kilifi officers after he lost the Kilifi South parliamentary ticket to businessman Ken Chonga
Gunmen have seriously wounded 73-year-old conservationist Kuki Gallmann at her conservation park in the latest of a string of attacks during land invasions in drought-stricken northern Kenya.

actor1: Police Forces of Kenya (2013-) General Service Unit
notes: Police engage communal gunmen who attacked a conservationist. Two killed
Supporters of MP Badi Twalib and aspirant Dan Aloo demonstrated outside a polling station over delays in the start of voting.

After voting delays in the ODM primary, supporters of MP Badi Twalib and aspirant Dan Aloo clashed outside Kwashee primary school polling centre. Mr Aloo' s supporters claimed the delays were to enable rigging.

Pokot raiders and police reservists engage in a firefight in Keiyo Valley on 22/04/2017. Four Pokot warriors and two civilians were killed in the shootout. According to the source, the attack could have been politically motivated and meant to intimidate communities not to take part in the Jubilee Coalition nominations.
Anti-riot police disperse angry voters at Hola who were prevented from voting by the agents of a gubernatorial aspirant
Youths stormed the Msambweni polling station demanding to know why names were missing from the ODM register.

Youths destroy ballot boxes and papers at Kiamugumo Primary School polling centre on 21/04/2017 disrupting the Jubilee Coalition primaries. They arrived to the polling station, when Anne Waiguru was voting, outpowering the police forces securing the station.
Youths barricaded the roads, stormed polling centres and burned ballot papers to protest the Jubilee primaries.
Police disperse crowds protesting the against the delayed polling material for the Jubilee primaries.
Voters in Kwanza burned their ballot papers to protest that the polls closed too early.
Voters burned their ballot papers in 5 polling stations in Laikipia East to protest the vote.

In Embu, voting in various parts was disrupted by a group of aspirants amid claims of rigging. Led by Runyenjes MP Cecily Mbarire and Manyatta MP John Muchiri, the aspirants stormed Kirimari Secondary School, where the ballot papers were being supplied, and demanded that the process be halted.
In Mau Summit, residents blocked the Kericho-Nakuru highway and the entrance to Mau Summit Secondary School protesting alleged vote rigging.
Youths barricaded the roads, stormed polling centres and burned ballot papers to protest the Jubilee primaries.
Youths barricaded the roads, stormed polling centres and burned ballot papers to protest the Jubilee primaries.
Residents of Imenti South block the Meru-Nairobi highway to protest over late arrival of ballot materials at Kaguru Agricultural Centre during the Jubilee Party primaries on April 21, 2017
A man is killed by land invaders near Laikipia Nature Conversatory
Scores are injured when unidentified armed youths launch a coordinated attack on a ODM meeting in Rongo.
Property destruction: A group of youths attacked a vehicle carrying ODM ballot materials in Mosando, Bogiakumu. The driver said he was blocked by individuals on motorbikes.
Violent protests and running battles with police occurred in Dandora after police shot a deaf boy they mistook for a robbery suspect. Injuries as a result of the protest are not known.
Three are injured when they are attacked by unidentified perpetrators during the night-time hours. The attack may be related to an election on 24/04. Date of attack not known - source dated 21/04.
Dr Thuo Mathenge and his supporters protest outside Jubilee Party headquarters in Pangani on April 19, 2017 over the outcome of Nyeri governorship nomination.
After Sonko's rally in Umoja, rioting youth pillaged shops.
Supporters for different aspirants for the Jubilee ticket in Ruiru clash.
A group protesting against vote rigging claims attacks a lawmaker's aide at Aberdares Country Club hotel, near Githunguri on the evening of 18/04.
A Jubilee parliamentary aspirant has been admitted at a Eldoret hospital after he was attacked by people said to be his rival's supporters.
Jubilee supporters held protests in Baringo (in Kabarnet town) following accusations that the primaries were rigged.
A Jubilee MP was shot at while he was campaigning in Nairobi. He has been hospitalised.
The aspiring ODM Naivasha candidate was arrested and held, and then admitted to hospital.
Members and supporters of ODM protest the use of IEBC registers during party primaries.
Non-violent activity: Mr Kenneth Kinyanjui, who is fighting for the Ikinu MCA's seat, went missing on Tuesday night before resurfacing on Tuesday
Sheila Githaiga, who is running for senate in Kieni, was ambushed and beaten by 30 men wielding batons and machetes.

Two factions of ODM clash, those loyal to Governor John Mruttu and those of National Assembly Minority Whip Thomas Mwadeghu, at a party meeting over vote tampering. The two sides also became violent on 16/04 over the choice of election clerks.
Supporters of two governor primary candidates (Joseph Ole Lenku and Tarayia Ole Kores) of the Jubilee party clashed on 17/04/2017 in Namanga. Seven people were injured but there were no fatalities.
ODM supporters of John Mbadi clash with those of Caroli Omondi at a party rally in Magunga on 17/04. Two reported injuries.

Two factions of ODM clash, those loyal to Governor John Mruttu and those of National Assembly Minority Whip Thomas Mwadeghu, at a party meeting over vote tampering. The two sides also became violent on 16/04 over the choice of election clerks.

Residents claim that in the last two months 10 people have been killed (4 in March, 6 in April) in raids on several villages in Lamu and Tana River counties. Though mainly related to cattle theft, a resident believes "some politicians were behind the raids."

Residents claim that in the last two months 10 people have been killed (4 in March, 6 in April) in raids on several villages in Lamu and Tana River counties. Though mainly related to cattle theft, a resident believes "some politicians were behind the raids."

Protests broke out in Kabete, Kiambu County on 15/04 following the disappearance of a parliamentary aspirant. The politician was reported missing the previous night, while his car, riddled with bullet holes, was found early Saturday in Gitaru. The fate of his person is not known.
ODM party has cancelled nomination results for Khwisero constituency due to irregularities, resulting in protests. No reports of violence
A father of four is killed by 200 'land invaders' that villagers claim had been invading land claiming they were squatters, only to later sell it to private developers.
Residents corner and kill a man accused of joining in on a land seizure in which a local was killed.

actor1: Police Forces of Kenya (2013-) General Service Unit
notes: Two General Service Unit (GSU) officers are reported missing following a weekend shootout with herders at Matweku near the Laikipia Nature Conservancy at the border of Laikipia and Baringo counties.
Pokot militia raided several villages in Marakwet East, but were repulsed by the police.
In Migori, unidentified youths invaded a rally in Sori Town on Saturday evening, forcing ODM activist Peter Jobando, a licensed firearm holder, to fire in the air several times.
Two suspected Islamist militants are killed in an extra-judicial killing by unidentified assailants in Naivasha. Both were suspected of recruiting and funding "terror" activities.
Non-violent activity: On Friday, the Kabete Jubilee parliamentary aspirant Charles Chege disappeared and resurfaced on Sunday morning
Pokot militia raided several villages in Marakwet East, but were repulsed by the police.
There were intense firefights between Pokot militias and government forces near Olmaiso, in Laikipia.

Supporters of MP Paul Otuoma of ODM protested the announcement of provisional results of the ODM Busia Governor nominations. Supporters shouted at the chairman of the county elections board and security agents had to take two men out of the hall, where the results where announced.
A female Jubilee aspirant who is running for Tetu parliamentary seat, is attacked by four masked men armed with metal bars and a gun at Mbaaini village.

Pokot raiders attacked Matweku police post in Ol Ari Nyiro Nature Conservancy, killing a police officer and abducting two others on 13/04/2017. Later the captured policemen were found dead at Kamwenje in Baringo. It is believed that the policemen were killed by Pokots.
A police officer and a civilian died in a firefight between Pokot militias and government forces near Olmaiso, in Laikipia, on 13/04/2017.
Gabra militia kills five Borana herders at Kubi Kalo; one on 11/04, four on 12/04.
Dozens of Kisumu residents protested over an alleged plot by the government to auction a local Sh4.2 billion mall.
ODM nominations in Busia County turned, with Deputy Governor Kizito Wangalwa's vehicle being smashed, its tires deflated and the driver attacked by rioting youth.
In Tharaka-Nithi, two supporters of Governor Samuel Ragwa were injured during the launch of Chuka/Igambangombe MP Muthomi Njuki's manifesto on April 12.
Gabra militia kills five Borana herders at Kubi Kalo; one on 11/04, four on 12/04.
At least seven Pokot were killed by police during a security operation in Tiaty, Baringo County. The gunmen were allegedly planning a livestock raid.
Non-violent activity: 10 April, 23:00EAT, Mandera, Kenya: al Shabaab militants entered Mandera and hijacked two pick-up trucks.
In a crackdown on "banditry", police set fire to a Pokot village. An infant dies during the raid.
Raiders kill one person in Pokot north during a peace meeting
4 people are killed by herders in Nakwomuru village in central Pokot county. Police reservists engage with the raiders, killing three of them.
4 people are killed by herders in Nakwomuru village in central Pokot county. Police reservists engage with the raiders, killing three of them
One person is feared dead and scores injured after supporters of Funyula MP Paul Otuoma and Busia Governor Sosepeter Ojamoong clashed in Funyula over the ODM primaries

Nominated Senator Elizabeth Ongoro led her supporters to protest the direct nomination handed to her rival at Orange House, the ODM headquarters in Nairobi. A plain clothed security officer was forced to shoot in the air to disperse the rowdy youths who had stormed the party Headquarters and were roughing up ODM Executive Director Oduor Ongwen.
Sex workers in Mombasa staged a protest after a colleague was murdered by a client.
Angry and rowdy youth chanting anti-Jubilee slogans disrupted the president's rally in Wajir and engaged the police. The police dispersed the rioters.
Pokot gunmen open fire at Ol Moran livestock market in bid to steal cattle. There are no references to injuries. But the police engage the gunmen in a battle later. No deaths reported
Sex workers protest at the deputy county commissioner's office demanding justice after a murder of a colleague.
The car of ODM politician Hassan Joho was attacked by gunmen. Joho's bodyguard was shot and injured but no fatalities is reported. Joho claims it to be an attempt of assasination.
Factions of ODM members clash during a rally. He groups were divided over support of Governor Zachary Okoth Obado and gubernatorial candidate Ochillo Ayacko.
Two Administration Police officers were attacked and set ablaze in Voi at the weekend when they were mistaken to be thugs.
Unidentified arsonists petrol-bombed the Migori ODM offices ahead of a party rally the following day.
Video released on socia media shows a police kill an unarmed man in Eastleigh on 31/03/2017. The victim was suspected of killing two police officers last month.

Residents of Kisumu protested peacefully over a delay in the opening of a mall. The opening has been delayed by ambiguities of bank loan payments. The protest was led by the director of Youth Reconciliation Forum of Kenya Eric Okello.

Property destruction: Suspected "cattle herders" burn down a tourist lodge on the Laikipia Plateau. The herders may have torched the lodge in retaliation to an ongoing security operation in the area. The hotel was empty at the time of the attack.
Movement of forces: Suspected Al-Shabaab hijacked a Kenyan government vehicle in the border town of Elwak in Mandera country. The attackers released the driver and reportedly drove into Somalia.
Mukutan Lodge was attacked by herders seeking pasture. They exchanged gunfire with the security forces and burned down the lodge.
When police blocked Hassan Joho's supporters and the press from following him into the police headquarters, the supporters protested in the streets of Mombasa.
Beach operators protest against a competitor's construction of a sea wall.
Two unidentified neighbouring communities clash in Garissa, along its border with Wajir over a boundary dispute. One bystander was reportedly killed in the clash. Date not clear - source dated 28/03.
A young boy is killed by armed raiders involved in a boundary dispute. It is not known in the victim was specifically targeted. Exact date not clear - source dated 28/03.
A boda boda driver on the Jubilee campaign was stabbed to death by a fellow campaigner over campaign payments. Attacker assumed to be Jubilee.
Kenyans in Namanga [border town] demonstrated against Tanzanian leader John Magufuli on Monday [27 March], saying he had deported their counterparts.

actor1: Police Forces of Kenya (2013-) General Service Unit
notes: An unidentified middle aged man who accessed a restricted area of the state house was shot by GSU.

Attackers believed to be from the Bahgere clan from Wajir South attacked Fadiwein village, which is inhabited by Auliyan community, injuring one. Eleven houses were also burnt and the attackers made away with 300 goats and five camels. The two communities had been fighting over a disputed boundary with the Bahgere, claiming the area falls under Wajir South, while Auliyan says it is in Garissa county.

Violence erupted in a political rally of the Orange Democratic Movement (ODM) on 27/03/2017 in Kendu Bay. Supporters of two rival politicians of the same party, Governor Cyprian Awiti and Mr. Oyugi Magwanga, clashed injuring three people. No fatalities.

At least two children were killed and three others injured on 25/03 after explosion went off in a unnamed village in Mandera county. Authorities suspect al Shabaab, though no group has claimed responsibility.

Following an alleged murder of a woman over a land dispute on 12/03/2017, villagers and the victim's family members attacked the houses of the suspects on 24/03/2017 in Riabotenene. Seven houses were burnt and their occupants were chased away. No fatalities.

The mother of Pastor Pius Muiru was found dead on 23/03/2017 in her farm in Karika village in Muranga. Police suspect that she was kidnapped and subsequently killed. Her son is the founder of an evangelical church and was the presidential candidate in 2007 for Kenya People's Party.
A Jubilee Party meeting attended by elected officials turned chaotic after their supporters clashed at the Bomas of Kenya over the election of the party's County Elections Board.
Police assault and arrest a journalist in Usengi. The scribe was targeted for investigating the use of excessive force by the officers who have been recently harming and harassing residents.
Ten people were killed and four injured in a cattle raid in Marti, Samburu, on 22/03/2017. It is believed to be a retaliatory attack run by thiefs of a neighbouring community.
Police officers "torture" a youth for unknown reason. A protest against the act followed.
Police officers "torture" a youth for unknown reason. A protest against the act followed.
Dozens of residents from Sook, West Pokot County held a protest in Kapenguria over corruption and mismanagement of the county's bursary fund.
A group of several minor political parties protest at the office of the electoral commission to demand a meeting with leadership in an effort of moving an electoral deadline.
A man suspected of being a thief was lynched by locals in Ngangarithi village in Nyeri town.
A NASA political aspirant was reportedly shot dead on 20/3. Location not known - party headquarters in Nairobi.
At least 10 people have been killed in Kom, Isiolo County between Borana and Samburu militias. The clash was spurred over drought.
Three are killed in a clash between Turkana and Samburu militias. The clash was sparked by revenge for cattle theft.
On 19/03 in Mukutani, four police officers were wounded when suspected Pokot herdsmen fired on their vehicle as they escorted members of the Ilchamus community to safety.
Kenya's president deployed the military to quell violence related to drought.
Lawmakers in the Mandera County Assembly clash over disagreements of a bill. Political parties not known.

Residents claim that in the last two months 10 people have been killed (4 in March, 6 in April) in raids on several villages in Lamu and Tana River counties. Though mainly related to cattle theft, a resident believes "some politicians were behind the raids."

Residents claim that in the last two months 10 people have been killed (4 in March, 6 in April) in raids on several villages in Lamu and Tana River counties. Though mainly related to cattle theft, a resident believes "some politicians were behind the raids."
Students at a Maseno school go on "rampage" over disagreements of their institution's leadership.
The KDF engaged Al Shabaab fighters at Kolbio.

assoc_actor_2: ICRC: International Committee of the Red Cross and Red Crescent
notes: Pokot fighters attacked a Red Cross convoy that was evacuating children injured in the attack on Mukutani the previous evening. 4 police officers were injured.
Jubilee supporters damaged property in Nairobi during the bids to select the election boards.
Jubilee supporters damaged property in Muranga during the bids to select the election boards.
Jubilee supporters damaged property in Nairobi during the bids to select the election boards.
One is dead and several others injured when supporters of Senator Elizabeth Ongoro and Ruaraka MP TJ Kajwang, both ODM, clash in Mathare.
A group protests poor security following a spate of attack from Somali "bandits."

In a continuance of ethnic violence, two Pokot woman are killed by suspected Tugen-Ilchamus raiders, after an attack on a police vehicle. It is not clear if the Pokot women were affiliated with the police, or if the police were simply caught in crossfire. In retaliation, Pokot militias soon after attacked Mukutan market, killing five women and four children and looting shops and homes. Other were reported injured.

In a continuance of ethnic violence, two Pokot woman are killed by suspected Tugen-Ilchamus raiders, after an attack on a police vehicle. It is not clear if the Pokot women were affiliated with the police, or if the police were simply caught in crossfire. In retaliation, Pokot militias soon after attacked Mukutan market, killing five women and four children and looting shops and homes. Other were reported injured.

In a continuance of ethnic violence, two Pokot woman are killed by suspected Tugen-Ilchamus raiders, after an attack on a police vehicle. It is not clear if the Pokot women were affiliated with the police, or if the police were simply caught in crossfire. In retaliation, Pokot militias soon after attacked Mukutan market, killing five women and four children and looting shops and homes. Other were reported injured.

Two are dead in a clash between Tugen-Ilchamus and Pokot group after the former attempted a raid to steal cattle in Baringo County. The clash lead to further ethnic violence in the following days. Exact location in Baringo was not reported by the source, though it stands to reason the violence occurred in Mukutani ward, as subsequent attacks occurred in Mukutan.

Auliyan militia attacked Duse centre in Isiolo County in a retaliatory attack following their expulsion for the area by government forces weeks prior. Five killed, six injured. Two of the attackers were shot and killed by police.

Auliyan militia attacked Duse centre in Isiolo County in a retaliatory attack following their expulsion for the area by government forces weeks prior. Five killed, six injured. Two of the attackers were shot and killed by police.
Members of Jubilee and NASA parties clash during a political convention. The unrest occurred on either 9 March or 10 March.
Auliyan militia attacked Garba Tula, killing a 70-year old man. The attack is believed to be related to revenge after being forces off land.
Al-Shabaab fighters have attacked a Kenyan military convoy at Lamu. Al Shabaab claimed killing four. Kenya acknowledged the attack, but said only one was killed.
Supporters of Homa Bay Governor Cyprian Awiti and Kasipul MP Oyugi Magwanga clash with crude weapons in Kendu Bay, leaving one seriously injured.

Police dispersed Kisumu Water and Sewerage Company (Kiwasco) employees after they held protests threatening to evict their director from office, grievance not clear. Police and protesters engaged in running battles.
Protest in the Rhamu over a proposed county budget.
Protests in the towns of Kotulo, Banisa and Takaba, Mandera County on 06/03 over a proposed government budget.
Protests in the towns of Kotulo, Banisa and Takaba, Mandera County on 06/03 over a proposed government budget.
Protests in the towns of Kotulo, Banisa and Takaba, Mandera County on 06/03 over a proposed government budget.

Armed raiders invading a ranch shot dead a Briton in northern Kenya's Laikipia County on the evening of 05/03. The victim was shot dead after he went to inspect the remains of a friend's home that had been burnt down by raiders on 03/03. Related, on 04/03, a police helicopter was shot at in the same farm as security officers carried out aerial surveillance. A second source claims the attack took place on 6 March.
On 04/03, a police helicopter was shot at by Pokot or Samburu raidersas security officers carried out aerial surveillance.
Property destruction: A UK national's home that had been burnt down by Pokot or Samburu raiders on 03/03.
Unidentified gunmen kidnapped three teachers from Dadaab camp. Al Shabaab have carried out abductions in the past, though it is not clear who the perpetrators were in this instance.

Traders and hawkers clashed on 01/03. A court order released on 24 February by the Milimani Commercial Courts had allowed the return of hawkers to trade on two streets in Eastleigh. Traders however protested the court's move leading to Wednesday's clashes.

Eight are dead in clashes between Tugen-Ilchamus and Pokot clans during the weeks of 26/02-12/03, exact dates, location and other details not known. Accounting for the activity between the clans in the present week, the fatality total stands at 21.

Jubilee Party youths opposed to the National Super Alliance (Nasa) have blocked Raila Odinga and Kalonzo Musyoka from addressing a rally at a scheduled venue. The mob on Monday used rocks to barricade the entrance to Meru town main stage, forcing the two leaders to keep off.
Protest against the state of roads block traffic in Kayole.
Residents torched 14 trucks and a Land Cruiser in Mariashoni, Molo after one of the truck drivers hit and killed a boda boda rider and his passenger.
Security forces kill a suspected al Shabaab member in Kwale and recover weapons.
A 45-year-old man was lynched on the weekend (25-26 February) when neighbours found him sleeping with the corpse of his 15 year old daughter in Molo Township.

Three suspected remnants of the Sabaot Land Defence Force were on 24/02 lynched by residents in Cheptais, Mt Elgon. The attackers also torched the suspects' houses. The attackers suspected the three recently murdered a man.
Boda boda riders in Maralal Town held demonstrations over alleged misappropriation of funds meant for construction of shades.
Three are killed in clashes over land in the Athi River area. Following, police made 92 arrests.

Security Measures: More than 30 schools have been closed due to persistent attacks by armed Pokot militia in Baringo county. Closed schools include Ngaratuko, Chemoe, Yatya, Tuluk, Kagir, Loruk, Chepkesin, Kapturo, Toboroi, Barsuswo and Lokorotabim in Baringo North.
Clinical officers in Narok County on 22/02 staged demonstrations and camped outside the county headquarters demanding promotions and harmonisation of their salaries.
Three are attacked and killed with blunt objects in Garissa on the night of 22/02. Perpetrators not known.
Striking universities lecturers hold a peaceful demonstrations in Nairobi to demand implementation of a 2013-2017 collective bargaining agreement.
On 22 February, a teacher was killed by Pokot militants in Chepkesin in Baringo North.

On 22 February, police found the bodies of four men in a vehicle in Gitaru. Police said they appeared to have been strangled to death and had visible injuries in their necks and faces. The reason for their deaths was not established.
On 22 February, one person was shot dead in Loruk by Pokot militants as 400 residents fled after their homes were set on fire.
Kilif nurses protest unpaid allowances.
Two more people were killed in Baringo county in attacks by armed Pokot militants. Specific details not provided.
On 19 February, Pokot militiants killed a young mother and her three-year old child at Natan in Baringo North. Another source reported that the attack took place on 21 February.

Residents of Nakuru took to the streets to protest the ownership of a piece of land in Mwariki. Police dispersed the more than 100 residents of Mutegi Estate who had blocked the Nakuru-Kiambogo road using stones.
On 18 February, two local leaders, MCA Kibet Cheretei and a Jubilee MP hopeful Pepe Kitambaa were shot dead by Pokot militants at a bar in Marigat town.

On 17 February, four people were seriously injured after suspected Pokot assailants attacked a bus carrying former Inspector General David Kimaiyo's relatives. The attack occurred on the Chesongoch-Liter road, near Tot trading centre.
A fight between a Pokot and Marakwet near Kerio River led to the death of one.

Armed youths disrupt an ODM rally in Katilia. Opposition leader Raila Odinga was speaking at the time of the attack. The youths were accused of being incited by MPs to disrupt the event. Police fired in the air to disperse the crowd. Injuries not known.
On 14 February, university lecturers protested in Nairobi after doctors were jailed for refusing to call off their strike. They are also protesting over low wages.
On 14 February, police fired teargas to disperse protesting youth from Mathare who barricaded the road over claims of illegal voter registration.
County workers protest a breach of government contract by dumping sewage at a county office.
Residents clash with police in Mugumoini village over a land surveying issue. A man was shot and injured.
A police officer was hacked to death at Mangala in Makueni County by a group of sand harvesters over the right to land.
At least 12 houses were torched in Pimbinyiet, Trans Mara West after clashes between two communities lasted over two days.
At least 12 houses were torched in Pimbinyiet, Trans Mara West after clashes between two communities lasted over two days.
Residents protest in Subukia after a student is killed the previous day by "thugs."
Youths protest during an address by the Kisii governor at Ekona. The demonstrators were demanding better government services.
On 8 February, an 82-year-old man who is the uncle of Kapseret MP was shot dead by heavily armed militants who raided his home in Kerio Valley.
On 8 February, a 43-year-old man was hacked to death in a dispute between two factions of a family over land in Kinangop, Nyandarua county. Four attackers, armed with pangas attacked the family home.
On 8 February, Samburu residents protested against Raila Odinga, burning posters and lighting bonfires.

Herders, illegally trespassing on land, injure a police officer and burn homes in Miteta, Ng'arua Division in Laikipia when they were confronted by a police. The violence comes 24 hours after a similar confrontation near Rumuruti.
Police shoot in the air and lob teargas canisters to disperse violent residents of Simba Chai in Teso South, Busia County who were protesting after they were allegedly denied national Identity cards.
Armed herders trespassing on illegal land shoot and injure a police officer after they were confronted near Rumuruti.
On 6 February, a protest was held over the death of a motorist who was hit by a speeding vehicle. Protesters called on the government to erect speed bumps.
Two public service vehicles were on 04/02 burnt down along Lang'ata Road in Nairobi by rioters after several had been in area accidents.

On 3 February, Eunice Wambui (aka Nyasuguta from Vitimbi), an actress who has been campaigning to become the MP for Embakasi South, was beaten with wooden rods by four political goons in Mukuru Kwa Ruben.

100+ gunmen believed to be al-Shabaab attacked a police post and destroyed communication masts in Arabia area, Mandera County. At least one bystander died in the attack. Number of other casualties not known, as al Shabaab had destroyed communication masts in the area. Shabelle Media Network reports an 'unknown number of police officers were killed.'
Tea farmers on Kirinyaga protest against the sale of company land. Location not known.
On 29 January, two suspected criminals were stoned to death by villagers at Othoro marke, Rachuonyo East subcounty.
Protesters force an ODM rally in Changamwe to end prematurely.
National Alliance supporters, specifically that of Senator Mike Sonko, attack journalists covering a visit from the Governor. Injuries reported. The attack occurred on or before 25/01.
Youth in Isiolo Town protest over what they termed as delays in the vetting process for issuing national identification cards.
A group of vigilantes attack and kill two they suspect of robbery.
A Kenya Police Reservist (KPR) was killed after suspected Al-Shabaab perpetrators hurled explosives at a bank and two hotels in Mandera town on the morning of 23/01.
On 22 January, residents in Kitungati village (Kitui) blocked police from removing the body of a man killed the day before by Somali militants.
Three are killed in a land dispute in Kanyakwar. The following day a group protest at the office of the "assistant chief", claiming he "had a hand in the dispute."

On 21 January, a man was shot in the waist and a woman was beaten after police clashed with squatters on disputed land in Nguu Tatu, Kisauni constituency, Mombasa. The squatters threw stones and shot arrows at police who lobbed teargas canisters to disperse them.
On 21 January, suspected Somali militia shot dead a herder in Ukasi, Kitui county.
Three are killed in a land dispute in Kanyakwar. The following day a group protest at the office of the "assistant chief", claiming he "had a hand in the dispute."

On 19 January, Egerton University lecturers protested in Nakuru. Lecturers in several parts of the country defied a court order and began their strike for the government to implement a 2013 pay rise agreement.

On 19 January, Machakos University lecturers protested on Makueni-Machakos road. Lecturers in several parts of the country defied a court order and began their strike for the government to implement a 2013 pay rise agreement. Machakos University lecturers protested on Makueni-Machakos road.
On 19 January, medical students in Nairobi protested disruptions to their studies during the doctors' strike.

Residents engaged police and Kenya Wildlife officers in running battles for most of Wednesday after a resident was killed by an elephant who had invaded a farm at Sironi village, Laikipia West Sub-County. The residents barricaded the busy Nyahururu-Ng'arua road at Maili Saba junction, causing a gridlock. The group demanded the government construct an electrified fence to protect them from further attacks.
On 16 January, Kowow clan and residents of Maron sub-location clashed. Several houses were torched in Marakwet East after the body of a 62 year old woman was found.
Two woman who were accused of witchcraft are lynched in Nyamokenye village, Nyamira on the evening of 14/01.

A suspect behind a spate of motorbike theft and rape cases was Friday lynched in Kelonget village in Bomet Central. Irate public set the man's house blaze before stoning him to death and setting his body on fire after an extended search.
Non-violent activity: Heavily armed Somali militia/herders are reported to have encorached onto farms in Kitui, armed with AK-47s and displaced unprotected farmer settlements.

A group of angered boda boda operators attack a full passenger bus, setting it alight. The boda boda rider were angered after a colleague was injured in an accident. All passengers escaped, no casualties.

A bystander student was killed on Sunday as renewed clashes between the Kipsigis and Maasai communities escalated at Pimbinyiet on the Trans Mara West-Trans Mara East border in Narok County. A similar clash took place at the location on 04/01.

Busia County residents have destroyed properties in protest to the killing of a boda boda rider by a police officer. torched a police Land Cruiser and four houses (three belonging to Administration Police officers and one for the chief). The driver had been shot during a traffic stop.
One is dead following clashes between Kipsigis and Maasai militias at Pimbinyiet on the Trans Mara West-Trans Mara East border in Narok County.

Residents blocked the Nyeri-Karatina road to protest rising accidents. The residents barricaded the road using stones and bonfires and urged the Kenya National Highway Authority to erect speed bumps to reduce the number of accidents.
On 2 January, Somali militants shot dead two herders in Inyanzae.
Residents block roads in protest of pollution of a nearby river.
A Kipsigis man is dead and others are injured following an attack from suspected Maasai militia at Esoit, Junction and Kirindon in Trans Mara West. Similar violence had occurred in recent weeks.

Non-violent activity: Pokot bandits have resorted to blocking roads using twigs and stones.
